===Etymology===

''Robot'' is from the Czech word ''[[robota]]'', which means [[drudgery]] or [[servitude]].  The word first appeared in the English language in a translation of the 1921 science-fiction play [[W:R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)|R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)]] by Karel Capek.

===Noun===
'''robot''' (plural: [[robots]])

